    </div>

    <h1 class="hero-title">Securing Web<br/><span>with Spring Security</span></h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">
      A full Spring Boot web application with authentication, protected routes,
      a custom login page, and a personal bio profile — built from scratch in 15 minutes.
    </p>

    <div class="hero-meta">
      <span>Spring Boot 3.x</span>
      <span>In-Memory Auth</span>
      <span>BCrypt Password Encoding</span>
      <span>Thymeleaf Templates</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- WHAT THIS DOES -->
  <section>
    <p class="section-label">// overview</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What This Project Does</h2>
    <div class="feature-grid">
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">🔐</div>
        <h3>Authentication Wall</h3>
        <p>Protected routes redirect unauthenticated users to a custom login page automatically.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">👤</div>
        <h3>Personal Bio Page</h3>
        <p>After login, users land on a profile page where they can write and save a bio about themselves.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">🔑</div>
        <h3>Secure Login & Logout</h3>
        <p>Custom login form with error feedback. Logout invalidates the session and redirects safely.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">🛡️</div>
        <h3>BCrypt Encryption</h3>
        <p>Passwords are never stored as plain text — BCrypt hashing is applied automatically.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

