        <div class="indent1 tree-new">├── MvcConfig.java <span class="tree-note">← URL → view mapping</span></div>
        <div class="indent1 tree-new">├── WebSecurityConfig.java <span class="tree-note">← security rules + users</span></div>
        <div class="indent1 tree-new">└── ProfileController.java <span class="tree-note">← bio page logic</span></div>
        <br/>
        <div class="tree-folder">📁 src/main/resources/templates/</div>
        <div class="indent1 tree-new">├── home.html <span class="tree-note">← public landing page</span></div>
        <div class="indent1 tree-new">├── login.html <span class="tree-note">← custom login form</span></div>
        <div class="indent1 tree-new">└── hello.html <span class="tree-note">← protected bio profile</span></div>
        <br/>
        <div class="tree-file">📄 pom.xml <span class="tree-note">← dependencies</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top:14px; font-size:0.8rem; color:var(--muted)">
      <span style="color:var(--accent)">■</span> Green files = created by me &nbsp;|&nbsp; Gray = auto-generated by Spring Initializr
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- KEY CONCEPTS -->
  <section>
    <p class="section-label">// concepts</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Key Spring Security Concepts</h2>
    <div class="concept-list">
      <div class="concept">
        <span class="concept-key">@EnableWebSecurity</span>
        <div class="concept-body">
          <h4>Activates Spring Security</h4>
          <p>Enables the full Spring Security framework for the application and integrates it with Spring MVC.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="concept">
        <span class="concept-key">SecurityFilterChain</span>
        <div class="concept-body">
          <h4>Route Access Rules</h4>
          <p>Defines which URLs are public and which require authentication. Acts as the traffic controller for all HTTP requests.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="concept">
        <span class="concept-key">BCryptPasswordEncoder</span>
        <div class="concept-body">
          <h4>Password Hashing</h4>
          <p>Encodes passwords with a one-way cryptographic hash. Even if the database leaks, plain passwords are never exposed.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="concept">
        <span class="concept-key">UserDetailsService</span>
        <div class="concept-body">
          <h4>User Store</h4>
          <p>Loads user data for authentication. Here we use an in-memory store — in production this connects to a database.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="concept">
        <span class="concept-key">Authentication object</span>
        <div class="concept-body">
          <h4>Who Is Logged In?</h4>
          <p>Spring injects the current user's session into controllers via the Authentication object — used to show the username and save bio per user.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- QUICK START -->
  <section>
    <p class="section-label">// run it yourself</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Quick Start</h2>
    <div class="steps-list">
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="step-n">1</div>
        <p><strong>Clone the repo</strong> — Download or clone this repository to your local machine.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="step-n">2</div>
        <p><strong>Open in IntelliJ IDEA</strong> — File → Open → select the <code>securing-web</code> folder.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="step-n">3</div>
        <p><strong>Wait for Maven</strong> — IntelliJ will auto-download all dependencies. Watch the bottom progress bar.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="step-n">4</div>
